[The fact that the case that occurred in Cote d'Ivoire was acquired in Guinea and brought into Cote d'Ivoire by land transport indicates that further spread into Burkina Faso is possible. One hopes that the laboratory tests are negative for this suspected case but increased surveillance, while results are awaited, is prudent.

It is reassuring to learn that the 58 possible contacts in Guinea are being followed and so far are negative for the infection. The circumstances under which the Guinea woman acquired her Ebola virus infection are still unclear, nor do we know the Ebola virus subtype involved. - Mod.TY

